-- 
Unicaja, Espana Duero Study Further Mergers, Expansion Reports

-- B y   S h a r o n   S m y t h
-- 
2011-12-10T10:09:02Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-10/unicaja-espana-duero-study-further-mergers-expansion-reports.html
Directors of the newly created bank
of Unicaja and Espana-Duero are studying plans to merge with
savings banks Liberbank and Caja 3,  Expansion  reported, citing
unidentified people with knowledge of the matter.  Braulio Medel, the president of Unicaja, and Evaristo del Canto, president of Espana Duero, will concentrate on starting
official negotiations with Caja 3 and Liberbank now that the
merger of the savings banks they presided over is complete, the
newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sharon Smyth in Madrid at 
 ssmyth2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew Blackman at 
 ablackman@bloomberg.net  